ce:section.ce:para:
Processing parameters will affect the stability and PL intensity of GQDs. While optimizing and verifying the process only one parameter was changed while other parameters were kept constant. Precursor concentration (1–2.5 g), irradiation time (Table 1), dispersing agent (Table 2
                           ), concentration and volume of dispersion medium (Tables 3 and 4

                           ); and temperature (40, 60, 80 °C) were optimized accordingly. Each variable parameter has a unique effect on stability and PL intensity of GQDs. The effects were compared by the visual assessment from UV cabinet to identify the luminescence produced and simultaneous observation of the UV–vis spectra of the sample.
